    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nSee title\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.o.number = true\r\nvim.o.signcolumn = 'no'\r\nvim.cmd.normal('o')\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('test'), 0, 0, {\r\n  number_hl_group = 'Error'\r\n})\r\n\r\nvim.fn.sign_define('foo', { text = 'F', numhl = 'Error' })\r\nvim.fn.sign_place(0, '', 'foo', vim.api.nvim_get_current_buf(), { lnum = 2 })\r\n```\r\n\r\n`nvim --clean -u min.lua`\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nSigns with `numhl` are always rendered regardless of `signcolumn`.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n v0.10.0-dev-879617c\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nNote: this was found via [Gitsigns's CI](https://github.com/lewis6991/gitsigns.nvim/actions/runs/6968414545/job/18962249567?pr=917). It might be a good idea to sanity future sign related PR's with this.",
